-- Finavera Wind Energy Sells 77-Megawatt Project to Innergex
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2012-07-26T14:35:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-26/finavera-wind-energy-sells-77-megawatt-project-to-innergex.html
Finavera Wind Energy Inc. (FVR) , a
Canadian wind-power developer, agreed to sell a 77-megawatt
project in northeast British Columbia to  Innergex Renewable
Energy Inc. (INE)   Innergex will pay about C$22 million ($21.8 million) for
the Wildmare Wind Energy Project, Vancouver-based Finavera said
in a statement today. The transaction is expected to close
within 60 days.  The project includes a 25-year power-purchase agreement
with British Columbia Hydro & Power Authority and is in the
advanced stages of permitting, according to the statement.  “This transaction illustrates the significant asset value
Finavera has created for shareholders and provides a strong
return on our investment in the development of wind energy for
British Columbia,” Finavera Chief Executive Officer Jason Bak
said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
